post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has lead to [high incarceration rates](https://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2016/jul/10/cory-booker/how-war-drugs-affected-incarceration-rates/) of otherwise inoffensive citizens. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In countries where "snus" is legal, the boxes has a compartment for spent product. This would disincetivized and lead to higher penalties if possession was illegal. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments invested a lot of money trying to cease drug use by everyone. It failed miserably. Not only it is not the most efficient way, but it is not even achievable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of this emotional harm is directly caused by erroneous negative perceptions of drug use like the ones being perpetrated here. Many people are unfairly vilified for responsibly using drugs, simply because they are illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, there were very few production standards \\(if any\\), meaning the consumer did not know what \\(potentially dangerous\\) conditions the alcohol had been manufactured in \\([pg. 4](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It is likely that a small group who are motivated not to take hard drugs solely because they are illegal would then try drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs could be legalised in government shops in which they could be administered through government pharmacists. This would allow governments to control access, much like the [Swedish alcohol trade](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systembolaget).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addictive drugs increasingly reduce one's ability to do without them, and therefore they can inhibit freedom. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, in the USA, there is a [pharmaceutical opioid crisis](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/us-opioid-epidemic). Drug companies and legal policies cannot be trusted to protect citizens. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Thousands of people [are killed](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/mexicos-drug-war) annually by drug cartels.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without producing all drugs locally inside that border and banning imports, the situation would continue to support foreign criminal activity, including associated acts of violence and social destabilisation in other places where drugs are produced but not legal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even though illegal drugs may still exist if drugs were legalised, there would be far less of them than when illegal drugs were the only option. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs deprives criminals of a substantial source of their income. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Cocaine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_harmfulness#/media/File:HarmCausedByDrugsTable.svg) is less harmful than alcohol, and only slightly more addictive. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The right to bodily integrity protects individuals from [forced labor, slavery or torture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodily_integrity).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The argument that illicit drugs can lead to addiction and should therefore be banned is a double standard, as various legal activities and substances are equally or even more addictive. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Aquiring drugs in a legal setting allows for regulation that may require informing the buyer about dangerous combinations, or avoid selling to people already under the influence of other drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although not all people are affected in this way, the risk for psychosis is higher [when regularly consuming cannabis with a high concentration of THC.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2801827/)'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In [many countries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulation_of_nicotine_marketing), the advertisement of cigarettes and alcohol is not allowed. The same model could be adopted in the regulation of legalized drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, addicts would be forced to buy legally, meaning there is a record of their usage and authorities can intervene if there is an instance of drug abuse.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Places that have decriminalised some or all drugs have not observed a long-term increase in consumption, and occasionally even a decrease has been observed. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation may reduce the price of drugs. This would have positive effects. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Date-rape drugs are controlled presently. The current prohibition has not hindered the occurrence of date rape.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. We could as soon prosecute people for being out of work, drinking, gambling or adultery."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Both of these "contracts" are often initiated under desperate circumstances or by ill informed people.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalising drugs related to date rape could bring the issue further into the public eye, allowing for more widespread education on the topic.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine, a commonly-used illegal drug, has [multiple negative health effects](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_intoxication) on the user.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Controlled substances, while controlled, are still obtained through the black market. Whether it is a date-rape drug or marijuana, legislation still cannot control whether illegal drugs are illegally obtained. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a false equivalency. Providing a service or good to bolster economic growth is not the same as being forced to give your money to the government.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation does not necessarily mean that drugs will be freely available. It is easier to control and regulate drugs when they are legalised as governments can restrict who can make and sell them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug cartels destabilize Latin America. With legalization they would disappear and Latin America would gain stability.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use has a negative effect on freedom and, therefore, ought to be contained.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The effects of different drugs play a role in the daily spending habits of drug users; thus more commonplace usage may change people's spending patterns in a way that negatively affects the economy."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If these substances legitimately are so dangerous, they _should_ primarily be considered weapons and not drugs. They can then be ignored in this discussion. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Due to abundance and normalization, people could enjoy other drugs like the enjoy a glass of wine. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The violence associated with alcohol was far greater during the prohibition when it was banned. The National Bureau of Economic Research says: "[increases in enforcement of drug and alcohol prohibition have been associated with increases in the homicide rate](https://www.nber.org/papers/w6950)".'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It will create jobs, not only in distribution but also in drug clinics and counseling centers. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Making it legal for companies to sell and market these drugs for recreational use without an understanding of the negative consequences that these substances cause is unethical. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The British Empire went to [war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opium_Wars) because they wanted to trade opium in China. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'True freedom of choice means that individuals must face the consequences of their actions, whether they are good or bad. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In countries where "snus" is legal, the boxes has a compartment for spent product. This would disincetivized and lead to higher penalties if possession was illegal. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine addiction causes [higher impulsivity](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5817335/), meaning sufferers are more likely to engage in risky behaviour such as gambling. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Right now \\(2019\\) children [as young as eight](https://www.channel5.com/show/8-years-old-and-smuggling-drugs/) are involved in the drug trade. This would not be allowed in a regulated market. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, in the USA, there is a [pharmaceutical opioid crisis](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/us-opioid-epidemic). Drug companies and legal policies cannot be trusted to protect citizens. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The ability to alter another person's mind state has potential for abuse, and utter manipulation. As a result, people will be more able to infringe on the bodily freedom/autonomy of others."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Private companies have a history of funding advertising supporting the use of products that are known to be dangerous to one's health, such as tobacco. I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Some adults may sell drugs to underaged people to make profit. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People who want to use drugs are largely already able to get access to them, but can have no assurance about their safety or quality. Government regulations could resolve this problem. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use will not cease regardless of the legal status. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since these would most likely be legally bought products, it would be much easier for the authorities have control over it, as opposed to illegally produced and smuggled goods.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Individuals who seek out "forbidden" activities will still seek that thrill and choose other illegal and possibly more dangerous activities to participate in. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government would be giving up authority to empower the individual. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the government cannot take responsibility for a dangerous activity which takes place in society, there is no guarantee anyone else will.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Psychedelics are often used for [one-off, recreational and spiritual](https://www.livescience.com/61902-psychedelic-drugs-change-personality.html) experiences. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs will lead to people having hallucinations or becoming violent. In these instances, individuals may be a danger to themselves or others. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an appeal to nature fallacy. Nature is not the word on what ought to be done with its products.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without producing all drugs locally inside that border and banning imports, the situation would continue to support foreign criminal activity, including associated acts of violence and social destabilisation in other places where drugs are produced but not legal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The availability of drugs is not the cause of suicides. It is just the means to do it. If they are not available other means will be found.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [global financial crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008) was caused by big companies acting with only their profits in mind, and the detrimental effects are still felt today. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's not a given that the low well-being of drug users' families are a result of the drug use. The confounding variable is likely mental health issues. It's possible \\(and sometimes preferable\\) to solve the mental health issues, while not stopping the drug use."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs may be adulterated despite legalisation, like [alcoholic beverages.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20959682) I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If this was true, cartels would already be moving over to newer, patented pharmaceuticals, whose costs of production is dwarfed by market price already.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Prohibition does not treat addicts, treatment, and prevention of addiction do. Both of these are accomplished far more effectively without the threat of incarceration for merely admitting use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
